<% content_for :title, "RoomScope — Site surveys for home technology pros" %>
<% content_for :head do %>
  <meta name="description" content="RoomScope helps smart home, AV, security, lighting, networking, and low-voltage pros capture room-by-room site surveys on iPhone and iPad, then generate customer-ready PDF reports and estimator handoffs.">
<% end %>

<main class="marketing-page">
  <section class="hero-section">
    <nav class="site-nav" aria-label="Main navigation">
      <a class="brand-mark" href="/" aria-label="RoomScope home">
        <span class="brand-icon">RS</span>
        <span>RoomScope</span>
      </a>
      <div class="nav-links">
        <a href="/support">Support</a>
        <a href="/privacy">Privacy</a>
        <a class="nav-cta" href="#beta">Request early access</a>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <div class="hero-grid">
      <div class="hero-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">Built for iPhone and iPad field walkthroughs</p>
        <h1>Room-by-room site surveys for home technology pros.</h1>
        <p class="hero-lede">
          Capture homeowner requests, system decisions, photos, and estimator flags during the walkthrough — then turn the visit into a customer-ready PDF and technical estimator handoff.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a class="button button-primary" href="#beta">Request early access</a>
          <a class="button button-secondary" href="#workflow">See the workflow</a>
        </div>
        <div class="trust-row" aria-label="Supported trades">
          <span>AV</span>
          <span>Security</span>
          <span>Lighting</span>
          <span>Networking</span>
          <span>Automation</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="product-card" aria-label="RoomScope app preview">
        <div class="ipad-frame">
          <div class="app-preview">
            <aside class="preview-sidebar">
              <div class="preview-label">Project</div>
              <strong>Smith Residence</strong>
              <p>New construction smart home</p>
              <div class="preview-step active">Room Survey</div>
              <div class="preview-step">Estimator Flags</div>
              <div class="preview-step">PDF Export</div>
            </aside>
            <section class="preview-main">
              <div class="preview-label">Kitchen</div>
              <h2>Capture the details before they get missed.</h2>
              <div class="system-grid">
                <div class="system-card selected">
                  <span>Requested</span>
                  <strong>Lutron scene control</strong>
                  <p>Keypad by pantry, dinner and cleanup scenes.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="system-card selected">
                  <span>Requested</span>
                  <strong>2-speaker audio zone</strong>
                  <p>Clean in-ceiling look, include customer note.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="system-card flagged">
                  <span>Estimator flag</span>
                  <strong>No visible wall clutter</strong>
                  <p>Keep controls minimal and confirm keypad locations.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="system-card">
                  <span>Photos</span>
                  <strong>3 attached</strong>
                  <p>TV wall, keypad wall, speaker location.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </section>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="problem-section">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">The gap</p>
      <h2>Apple Notes and photos are not enough for estimating.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="problem-grid">
      <article>
        <h3>Owner intent gets buried</h3>
        <p>Homeowner preferences, “must not miss” details, and room-specific decisions get scattered across notes, texts, and memory.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3>Photos lack context</h3>
        <p>Photos are valuable, but estimators still need to know which room, which system, and why the photo matters.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3>Handoffs are inconsistent</h3>
        <p>RoomScope structures the walkthrough so the estimator sees flags, open questions, captions, and customer-facing notes in one place.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="workflow" class="workflow-section">
    <p class="eyebrow">Workflow</p>
    <h2>From field walkthrough to estimator handoff.</h2>
    <div class="workflow-grid">
      <article>
        <span class="step-number">01</span>
        <h3>Walk room by room</h3>
        <p>Start from default room templates or add custom rooms as you move through the home.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span class="step-number">02</span>
        <h3>Capture systems clearly</h3>
        <p>Mark requested, future, discuss, or skip for TV, audio, lighting, shades, network, security, cameras, and more.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span class="step-number">03</span>
        <h3>Flag what estimating must see</h3>
        <p>Highlight owner requests, open questions, site constraints, and captioned photos before they are forgotten.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span class="step-number">04</span>
        <h3>Share a clean report</h3>
        <p>Generate a customer-ready PDF with a technical appendix for estimator handoff and internal follow-up.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="ipad-section">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">iPad-friendly by design</p>
      <h2>Great for teams that already carry iPads into the field.</h2>
      <p>
        RoomScope starts with fast iPhone capture, but the workflow is a natural fit for iPad: project context, active room capture, flags, and report readiness can sit side-by-side during a walkthrough.
      </p>
    </div>
    <ul class="feature-list">
      <li>Offline-first local capture for real job sites.</li>
      <li>Structured templates for new construction and retrofit projects.</li>
      <li>Photo appendix with captions and estimator flags.</li>
      <li>Room readiness indicators before leaving the site.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-section">
    <p class="eyebrow">Early beta</p>
    <h2>Help shape RoomScope before the App Store launch.</h2>
    <p>
      If your team sells or estimates smart home, AV, low-voltage, security, lighting, networking, or automation projects, we would like your field workflow feedback.
    </p>
    <%= render "beta_signups/form", beta_signup: @beta_signup || BetaSignup.new %>
  </section>

  <footer class="site-footer">
    <span>© 2026 RoomScope</span>
    <a href="/support">Support</a>
    <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>
  </footer>
</main>
